verbs.description: overcertify (third-person singular simple present overcertifies, present participle overcertifying, simple past and past participle overcertified)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To certify beyond the actual value.
examples: The Bank of the Commonwealth suspension resulted from overcertifying the checks of its former president, Edward Haight, to the amount of $225,000, of which Mr. Haight could only make good $60,000.
